  management: ["Administer IV antibiotics precisely on schedule as prescribed (typically 4-8 weeks)", "Maintain seizure precautions throughout hospitalization", "Monitor for signs of increased ICP (HOB 30 degrees, head midline)", "Prepare patient for possible stereotactic aspiration or craniotomy", "Monitor surgical drain output if present (color, amount, consistency)", "Administer prescribed anticonvulsants and monitor therapeutic levels"],
